 {"id":"frankenjax-cn41","title":"Pad overflows output dimension for huge zero-element shapes","description":"eval_pad computes interior_span = (dim - 1) * interior and out_dim = low + dim + interior_span + high with unchecked i64 arithmetic. Valid zero-element tensors can have huge nonzero dimensions paired with a zero dimension, so padding a shape like [u32::MAX, 0] with a very large interior padding on axis 0 can panic in debug builds or wrap in optimized builds before the existing u32 bound check. Expected: compute padded dimensions with checked arithmetic and return a typed EvalError on overflow; add a regression that does not allocate.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T08:22:34.200605736Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T08:28:25.504374274Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T08:28:25.502577194Z","close_reason":"Checked pad dimension arithmetic and output element counts before allocation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
