 {"id":"frankenjax-cyt","title":"Handle complex max/min with magnitude comparison (fj-lax arithmetic.rs)","description":"WHAT: Add complex max and min to eval_binary_elementwise_complex() in crates/fj-lax/src/arithmetic.rs:179-191.\nWHERE: The match at line 183-191 only allows add/sub/mul/div through; max/min hit the catch-all error at line 186.\nHOW: JAX uses lexicographic comparison on (real, imag) for complex max/min. Implement: compare real parts first, then imag parts for tiebreaking. Return the element that \"wins.\" This matches numpy.maximum/minimum behavior for complex.\nWHY: Without this, vmap or reduce operations on complex tensors that use max/min will fail. JAX handles this case.\nDEPENDS ON: None (independent of pow/rem/atan2).\nTESTING: Test complex max/min: max((1+2i), (3+0i)) = (3+0i); min((1+2i), (1+1i)) = (1+1i). Edge case: equal real parts resolved by imag.\nACCEPTANCE: No \"complex arithmetic not yet implemented\" string in eval_binary_elementwise_complex for max/min.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T23:27:23.139602679Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T00:23:05.987304407Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T00:23:05.987053082Z","close_reason":"Completed: implemented complex max/min in fj-lax with lexicographic comparison and direct tests; rch cargo test -p fj-lax passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
